   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "19a15fa1",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "#### Problem Statement:\n",
    "\n",
    "Every year a lot of companies hire a number of employees. The companies invest time and money in training those employees, not just this but there are training programs within the companies for their existing employees as well. The aim of these programs is to increase the effectiveness of their employees. But where HR Analytics fit in this? and is it just about improving the performance of employees?\n",
    "\n",
    "\n",
    "\n"
   ]
  },

   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Splitting the variables\n"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 114,
   "id": "4e92ef26",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "only_f=df2.drop('Attrition',axis=1)\n",
    "lbl =df2['Attrition']\n"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "4d030405",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## we need to balance the data set"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "f3218893",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Using the over sampling techniques for class imbalance\n"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 115,
   "id": "052fe51c",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "from imblearn.over_sampling import SMOTE\n",
    "smt=SMOTE()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 116,
   "id": "f0e09971",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "train_x,train_y=smt.fit_resample(only_f,lbl)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 117,
   "id": "497333c0",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "text/plain": [
       "1    1233\n",
       "0    1233\n",
       "Name: Attrition, dtype: int64"
      ]
     },
     "execution_count": 117,
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "execute_result"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "#after Applying SMOTE\n",
    "train_y.value_counts()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "ba47948a",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Now Dataset is Balanced .\n"

    "print('percentage of loss of data by zscore is :',(df3.shape[0]-df4.shape[0])/df3.shape[0])"

    "from sklearn.preprocessing import PowerTransformer\n",
    "from sklearn.preprocessing import MinMaxScaler\n",
    "from sklearn.pipeline import Pipeline"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 2,
   "id": "c5c4b17d",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "scaler=MinMaxScaler(feature_range=(1,2))\n",
    "power=PowerTransformer(method='box-cox')\n",
    "pipeline=Pipeline(steps=[('s',scaler),('p',power)])"
   ]
  },

  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "e18aaa5c",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## VIF(Variance Inflation Factor)\n"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 130,
   "id": "c6f422f1",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "from statsmodels.stats.outliers_influence import variance_inflation_factor"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 131,
   "id": "d22d62aa",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "def vif():\n",
    "    vif=pd.DataFrame()\n",
    "    vif['Variables']=x.columns\n",
    "    vif['VIF Factor']=[variance_inflation_factor(x.values,i)for i in range(x.shape[1])]\n",
    "    return vif"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",

    "#classification models\n",
    "from sklearn.linear_model import LogisticRegression\n",
    "from sklearn.naive_bayes import GaussianNB\n",
    "from sklearn.tree import DecisionTreeClassifier\n",
    "from sklearn.neighbors import KNeighborsClassifier\n",
    "from sklearn.svm import SVC\n",
    "from sklearn.ensemble import RandomForestClassifier\n",
    "from sklearn.ensemble import AdaBoostClassifier\n",
    "from sklearn.ensemble import GradientBoostingClassifier\n",
    "\n",
    "#model selection\n",
    "from sklearn.model_selection import train_test_split\n",
    "from sklearn.model_selection import cross_val_score\n",
    "from sklearn.model_selection import GridSearchCV\n",
    "\n",
    "#Metrics\n",
    "from sklearn.metrics import accuracy_score\n",
    "from sklearn.metrics import classification_report\n",
    "from sklearn.metrics import confusion_matrix\n",
    "from sklearn.metrics import roc_curve,roc_auc_score"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 144,
   "id": "fe4b96db",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "lg=LogisticRegression()\n",
    "gnb=GaussianNB()\n",
    "dtc=DecisionTreeClassifier()\n",
    "knc=KNeighborsClassifier()\n",
    "svc=SVC()\n",
    "rfc=RandomForestClassifier()\n",
    "abc=AdaBoostClassifier()\n",
    "gbc=GradientBoostingClassifier()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 145,
   "id": "6f6676dc",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "list_model=[lg,gnb,dtc,knc,svc,rfc,abc,gbc]"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 146,
   "id": "32e3ffd5",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "def confusion_plot():\n",
    "    print('accuracy_score:-',accuracy_score(pred,y_test))\n",
    "    print(classification_report(pred,y_test))\n",
    "    matrix = confusion_matrix(pred,y_test)\n",
    "    sns.heatmap(matrix, annot=True, fmt=\"d\", cmap='Blues', square=True)\n",
    "    plt.xlabel(\"predicted\")\n",
    "    plt.show()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 147,
   "id": "2e2cbca3",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "accuracy_score:- 0.8670694864048338 Random state:- 43\n"
     ]
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "maxacc=0\n",
    "maxrn=0\n",
    "\n",
    "for i in range(1,100):\n",
    "    x_train,x_test,y_train,y_test=train_test_split(x,y,test_size=.30,random_state=i)\n",
    "    lg.fit(x_train,y_train)\n",
    "    pred=lg.predict(x_test)\n",
    "    score=accuracy_score(pred,y_test)\n",
    "    if score>maxacc:\n",
    "        maxacc=score\n",
    "        maxrn=i\n",
    "print('accuracy_score:-',maxacc,'Random state:-',maxrn)"
   ]

    "def confusion_plot1():\n",
    "    print('accuracy_score:-',accuracy_score(grid_pred,y_test))\n",
    "    print(rfc_grid.best_estimator_)\n",
    "    print(rfc_grid.best_params_)\n",
    "    print('\\nClassification Report')\n",
    "    print(classification_report(grid_pred,y_test))\n",
    "    matrix = confusion_matrix(grid_pred,y_test)\n",
    "    sns.heatmap(matrix, annot=True, fmt=\"d\", cmap='Blues', square=True)\n",
    "    plt.xlabel(\"predicted\")\n",
    "    plt.show()"
